radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is enlarged measuring up to 10 mm with mural thickening and mucosal hyperemia, adjacent fat stranding; at least 2 adjacent cecal diverticula with one inflamed. Findings favor acute diverticulitis with micro perforation. There is fluid within the endometrial canal, which is normal in a patient of this age. Otherwise, visualized organs and structures are unremarkable.
